social_posts.post_text: A billion is a lot. It takes a huge team to make it go and I’m incredibly thankful for mine at @houseof42_ and @sonynashville. Thank you especially to everyone who has loved one or all of my songs, it’s been an incredible year and seeing this press release (in bio) come across the ticker made me smile and remember a whole lot of great times making music. Happy holidays, Merry Christmas and the like. See you sometime next year✌🏼

Thankful today to be a part of the number one song in the country. Years ago before we had anything going in music, Jordan and I sat down to write a song and he told me it was his first ever co-writing session. Now all this time later we have written some great ones and have a number one song together and it just feels so great to look back on the journey. I’ve known Drag since college and now we’ve written songs together all over the world and this is our first number 1 together. I’m so grateful of this one and proud of who I got to make it with. Anyway, I’m in Nashville making music and it feels like it’s where I’m supposed to be right now. I feel inspired for the first time in a long time. Love and peace to all of you, have a smile this Tuesday afternoon. Jet Skis for everyone.

Favorite picture in our house. Happy 5 years, MM. Lots of music, lots of places, lots of great times and a baby. It’s been the greatest. Blessings to each and every one of you. Give your person a big hug and tell ‘em you love them today.

Playing an acoustic show in the home state for a great cause. This might be my only show of the year. Tickets on-sale Friday, May 19th @ 10am EST, link to purchase in my bio. See you in August, West Michigan.

Ace Paloma’s with Dobel Tequila and Owen’s Rio Red Grapefruit will be flowing all tournament long 🎾🍹

She deserves to be celebrated, not just tolerated. I love the response from people who don’t just love these two songs, they needed them. I knew it would strike a chord. Most people would just shut up and keep collecting the paycheck, because the wave of vitriol is real and it’s hard. I’m so sick of watching my wife get the shit kicked out of her by the internet. I’m sick of every talking head having some kind of stupid opinion about what she says. It’s the same every time, why are you surprised when she calls out something racist or homophobic, I’m sick of people getting rewarded for it. To me the Bridge is beautiful and so rock and roll. She deserves a little sunshine for the burden she has carried for every artist and fan that feels the same way. I can’t wait for that first tour and to see all of the smiling and beautiful people who needed these songs and and also need HER. I can’t wait to make music that follows the same path, whatever that is. Feel free to leave a comment below to express your hatred or love for whatever I said, they will be duly noted, filed, sorted, and discarded. Love you, MM. Keep on keepin’ on.
